      The <methodname>get_escape_char</methodname>() method gets the value of the ESC character in the given <parameter>language</parameter>.
	  </para>
  </refsect2>

  <refsect2 id="method-gtksourcelanguage--get-mime-types">
    <title>gtksourceview.SourceLanguage.get_mime_types</title>
    <programlisting><methodsynopsis language="python">
	  <methodname>get_mime_types</methodname>
	  <methodparam></methodparam>
	  </methodsynopsis></programlisting>
      
    <variablelist>
	    <varlistentry>
	      <term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term>
	      <listitem><simpara> a list of mime types (strings).</simpara></listitem>
	    </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para>
      The <methodname>get_mime_types</methodname>() method returns a list of mime types for the given <parameter>language</parameter>. 
      After usage you should free each element of the list as well as the list itself.
	  </para>
  </refsect2>

  <refsect2 id="method-gtksourcelanguage--set-mime-types">
    <title>gtksourceview.SourceLanguage.set_mime_types</title>
    <programlisting><methodsynopsis language="python">
	  <methodname>set_mime_types</methodname>
	  <methodparam><parameter role="keyword">mime_types</parameter></methodparam>
	  </methodsynopsis></programlisting>
      
    <variablelist>
	    <varlistentry>
	      <term><parameter role="keyword">mime_types</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
	      <listitem><simpara> a list of mime types (strings).</simpara></listitem>
	    </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para>
      The <methodname>set_mime_types</methodname>() method sets a list of <parameter>mime_types</parameter> for the given 
      <parameter>language</parameter>. If <parameter>mime_types</parameter> is <literal>None</literal> this function 
      will use the default mime types from the language file.
	  </para>
  </refsect2>

